# API Layer

Every endpoint follows:

Controller

↓

Repository

↓

Datasource

↓

API Client

Never bypass the Repository.

---

# DTOs

Every endpoint owns:

Request DTO

Response DTO

Mapper

Never expose DTOs outside Infrastructure.

---

# Endpoint Naming

Example

GET

/courses

GET

/courses/{id}

POST

/auth/login

POST

/quiz/submit

Use REST conventions.

---

# Errors

Map every HTTP error into Domain Failures.

Never expose DioException.

---

# Pagination

Standard response

items

page

limit

total

hasMore

Cursor should generate pagination automatically.

---

# Streaming

Support streamed AI responses.

Do not wait for complete payloads.

---

# Cursor Instructions

Always generate:

Datasource

DTO

Mapper

Repository

Tests